cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper proposes a convolutional network regression method for quantifying enlarged perivascular spaces (EPVS) in the basal ganglia from 3D brain MRI. The method involves segmentation of the basal ganglia and the use of a 3D convolutional regression network designed for small object detection within this region of interest. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, specifically a convolutional neural network, for regression analysis. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the investigation of hyper-parameters and the evaluation of the reproducibility of the network, which are common topics in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper discusses the potential clinical implications of the automatic quantification of EPVS, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
